<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">About</h1>

<p>Welcome to the NBA Management Application. This application allows users to manage and view information about NBA teams, players, their statistics, and classifications.</p>

<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-4">Features</h2>
<ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4">
  <li>View a list of all NBA teams and their details.</li>
  <li>View a list of all players and their respective teams.</li>
  <li>Access detailed statistics for each team’s players.</li>
  <li>View the classification (wins and losses) for each team.</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-4">Database Relationships</h2>
<p>The application uses a relational database with the following models and relationships:</p>

<h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-2">Team</h3>
<p>A Team has many Players and one Classification. Teams can be associated with multiple games through their players.</p>

<h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-2">Player</h3>
<p>A Player belongs to a Team and has many Statistics. Players can participate in multiple games through the GamePlayer join table.</p>

<h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-2">Statistic</h3>
<p>Statistics are associated with a Player and include data such as points, rebounds, and assists.</p>

<h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-2">Classification</h3>
<p>A Classification belongs to a Team and includes the number of wins and losses for the team.</p>

<h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-2">Game</h3>
<p>A Game has many players through the GamePlayer join table and includes information about the game´s date and location.</p>

<h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-2">GamePlayer</h3>
<p>GamePlayer is a join table that connects Players to Games, allowing for a many-to-many relationship between Players and Games.</p>

<p class="mt-4">We hope you find this application useful for managing and viewing NBA-related data.</p>
